# Generated output files from examples and tests
*.gle
*.pdf
*.eps
*.png
data_*.dat
test_graphics_output/
test_custom_prefix_output/

# ... but shipped example figures ARE tracked (the GUI guide references
# them; without these negations the example .gle/.dat silently never
# reached the repository).
!examples/**/*.gle
!examples/**/data_*.dat
# ... the imshow/grid-contour examples ship gleplot-written .z grid sidecars.
!examples/**/*.z
# ... but GLE's own build products are NOT source and must stay untracked even
# though they match the negations above (a later rule wins):
#   - contour derivatives  <base>-cdata.dat / -clabels.dat / -cvalues.dat
#   - fitz-gridded grids    <prefix>_points<N>.z  (GLE generates these at
#     compile time from the tracked <prefix>_points<N>.dat triples)
examples/**/*-cdata.dat
examples/**/*-clabels.dat
examples/**/*-cvalues.dat
examples/**/*_points*.z
examples/outputs/
tests/output/
docs/source/_static/gallery/

# ... and the shipped GUI/app icon asset is tracked despite the *.png rule
# above (it is the source of truth for the packaged .ico/.icns).
!src/gleplot/gui/assets/*.png
